  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An App Clip gives users quick access to a particular workflow in your app, even when the user hasn’t installed your app. NFC readers, App Clip Codes, or QR codes define an "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "invocation URL"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " that specifies which App Clip, or workflow within your full app, the system needs to run. Before launching the App Clip, the system ensures that the App Clip includes in its code signature, an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/bundleresources/entitlements/com_apple_developer_associated-domains"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", which cites the invocation URL’s domain. The system also verifies that the server of the domain agrees to launch the App Clip, by citing the App Clip within an Apple App Site Association File that it hosts."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-3706576",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "3706576",
                "title": "Figure 1"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To associate your app and App Clip with your website:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Specify your invocation URL’s domain within an "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/bundleresources/entitlements/com_apple_developer_associated-domains"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " on both your app and App Clip targets in Xcode."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Add or modify an Apple App Site Association (AASA) file on the domain’s server."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The system verifies that both the entitlement and the configuration in the AASA file match before it permits the invocation of the App Clip. App Store Connect also verifies the match when you create an App Clip experience; for more information, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "Set Up an App Clip Experience",
              "destination": "https://help.apple.com/app-store-connect/#/dev5b665db74"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "You may already be familiar with the Associated Domains Entitlement if your app supports "
                },
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "title": "Handoff",
                  "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/handoff/"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " or "
                },
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "title": "universal links",
                  "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/ios/universal-links/"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". If you’re new to using this entitlement and universal links, read "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/xcode/allowing-apps-and-websites-to-link-to-your-content"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/xcode/supporting-universal-links-in-your-app"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". For additional information about the Associated Domains Entitlement — including cache policies —, read "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/xcode/supporting-associated-domains"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "tip"
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": " Add the Associated Domains Entitlement",
          "anchor": "3706575"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "No matter which invocations you choose to support and which invocation URLs you use, you must add the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/bundleresources/entitlements/com_apple_developer_associated-domains"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to the app and the App Clip targets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "First, open your project in Xcode; then, in your project settings, enable the Associated Domains capability to add the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/bundleresources/entitlements/com_apple_developer_associated-domains"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Second, for each URL that launches your App Clip or full app, add its domain to the Associated Domains capability using this pattern: "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "appclips:<fully qualified domain>"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". For example, add "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "appclips:example.com"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " or "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "appclips:appclip.example.com"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Make sure to only include the desired subdomain and the top-level domain. Don’t include a trailing slash ("
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "/"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "), wildcard ("
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "*"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "), or path and query components in the URL. For more information, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/xcode/supporting-associated-domains"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Make Changes to Your Server",
          "anchor": "3706570"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In addition to adding the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/bundleresources/entitlements/com_apple_developer_associated-domains"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to your Xcode project, you need to make changes to your server to associate your App Clip with your server and allow the system to verify the URL that tries to invoke your App Clip."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "First, create an AASA file as described in "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/xcode/supporting-associated-domains"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Next, add an entry for the App Clip with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "appclips"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " key to the file."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The following code shows the content to add. Note how the value for the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "apps"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " key is an array that contains the app identifier of the App Clip. In many cases, the array contains only one entry. However, it can contain entries for multiple App Clips."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "{",
            "    \"appclips\": {",
            "        \"apps\": [\"ABCDE12345.com.example.MyApp.Clip\"]",
            "    }",
            "...",
            "} "
          ],
          "syntax": "other",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3706572",
            "title": "Listing 1"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "For apps that detect App Clip Codes in AR, add an entry for the parent app identifier. For more information, see "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/app_clips/interacting_with_app_clip_codes_in_ar"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "important"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Then, add the AASA file to your website’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": ".well-known"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " directory. If you previously added an AASA file to your server, add the entry for the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "appclips"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " key to the existing file."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "If you plan to use multiple invocation URLs with different domains, remember to add an AASA file to each domain’s "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": ".well-known"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " directory. In addition, remember to add each domain to the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/bundleresources/entitlements/com_apple_developer_associated-domains"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Finally, to make sure the system can validate the association between your App Clip and the AASA file on your server, check your server’s configuration and make sure it allows "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "AASA-Bot"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "CFNetwork"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " as user agents."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Check the Validation Status of Your App Clip",
          "anchor": "3706566"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "App Store Connect verifies the AASA file configuration of your App Clip after you’ve uploaded a build to App Store Connect and created an App Clip experience. To check the verification status:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Open "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "link",
                      "title": "App Store Connect",
                      "destination": "https://appstoreconnect.apple.com/"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " in your browser and navigate to a build’s details page."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Click View Status in the App Clip section to show the domain validation status. It shows the validation status for each domain that’s associated with your App Clip."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For example, you could configure the default App Clip experience to use "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "https://example.com"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " as its invocation URL and configure an advanced App Clip experience to use "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "https://appclip.example.com"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". In this example, you’d place an AASA file in the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": ".well-known"
            },
